## Scope

This slice adds the pure analysis/derivation layer that reads the engine's solver outputs and presents the §4 quantities. It is predominantly reuse: the 4×4 solver, the field model, the math seam, and the 1D/3D sweep+chart pipeline already exist and MUST NOT be forked or re-derived. The genuinely net-new work is narrow and named in 010: completing the commented-out per-`EmField` Mueller member, deriving ellipsometric Ψ/Δ and (N, C, S) from the existing s/p amplitudes, an explicit per-layer absorptance / total-absorbed-power breakdown from the Poynting flux, a CIE XYZ/Lab/sRGB conversion from an R or T spectrum, and the in-layer field/EFI depth profile assembled from the existing `EmField.propagate` seam. All new functions are pure functions of a `Solution` (or of the field amplitudes inside it), computed in canonical SI internally.

These functions land in the engine's existing `Analytics` project (NOT in the `OpticalConstructor.*` projects), plus one edit to the engine `FieldFunctions.fs` completing the `member em.muellerMatrix` at line 93. This slice is foundational for later parts: Part G reuses §F.5 `psiDelta` for fit residuals, and Part H uses §F.6 `fieldDepthProfile` and §F.8 colorimetry.

**Note (gates).** This slice touches the engine `Analytics`/`Berreman` tree only; the relevant runtime gate is `unit-tests` (`BerremanTests`) plus `build`. No new C# project is introduced; these are pure F# modules with no UI and no FuncUI reference, so the clone audit gate of Part A §A.9 is unaffected and remains undecided (per F.10).

## Requirements

### R-1. §F.1 [Core] Spectral & angular R/T/A scans (s/p split) MUST reuse the existing `OpticalFunction` outputs and the `calculate` sweep

The spectral/angular scan of R, T, and the s/p split MUST be produced by `Variables.calculate` (`Variables.fs:237`) driven by a `WaveLengthRange` or `IncidenceAngleRange` `RangedVariable` (`Variables.fs:42,43,46`), reading the per-point `Solution.func` outputs `R`, `Rp`, `Rs`, `T`, `Tp`, `Ts` (`FieldFunctions.fs:130-135,192`). The absorption channel A = 1 − R − T MUST be a new pure function `absorptance (s : Solution) : float` placed in a new module file `Analytics/AnalysisFunctions.fs`, computed as `(s.func R, s.func T) |> fun (r, t) -> 1.0 - (defaultArg r 0.0) - (defaultArg t 0.0)`; it MUST reuse `Solution.func` and MUST NOT call the solver again. The s/p split is already carried by the distinct `Rp`/`Rs`/`Tp`/`Ts` cases — no new split logic is admitted. This directive adds NO new sweep engine: 1D scans go through `calculate`/`plot` (`Variables.fs:237`, `Charting.fs:21`) and the 2D R-vs-λ×angle surface goes through `calculate3D`/`plot3D` (`Variables.fs:270`, `Charting.fs:64`).

### R-2. §F.2 [Core] Parameter sweeps MUST be expressed as `RangedVariable` cases, not a new sweep abstraction

Sweeps over thickness, angle, polarization, ellipticity, wedge angle, or an arbitrary model parameter MUST be expressed by constructing the existing `RangedVariable` (`Variables.fs:42`): `IncidenceAngleRange`, `PolarizationRange`, `EllipticityRange`, `WaveLengthRange`, `WedgeAngleRange`, and — for thickness or any material parameter — `ArbitraryVariableRange` carrying an `ArbitraryVariable` (`Variables.fs:32`) whose `getSys : OpticalSystem -> double -> OpticalSystem` mutates the system at each sweep point. The UI/orchestration layer MUST build these values; this part MUST NOT introduce a parallel sweep descriptor type. Bulk sweep output (the `array<float * Solution>` from `calculate`, or the 2D array from `calculate3D`) MUST be persisted ONLY as a `.binz` sidecar via `Softellect.Sys.Core.serialize` with `BinaryZippedFormat` (`C:/GitHub/Softellect/Sys/Core.fs:257`) per Part A §A.7 — never inside the canonical JSON project. No retry, resume, or incremental-cache layer is added.

### R-3. §F.3 [Standard] Complete the commented-out per-`EmField` Mueller path and add the Stokes/Jones/Mueller accessors

The commented-out member `member em.muellerMatrix : MuellerMatrix` at `FieldFunctions.fs:93` MUST be implemented by delegating to the existing constructor `MuellerMatrix.fromEmFields` (`Fields.fs:636`), supplying the field's own s- and p-resolved components — it MUST NOT re-derive the 4×4 Mueller algebra, which already exists at `MuellerMatrix.create` (`Fields.fs:601`). The system-level Mueller matrices MUST be obtained from the already-implemented `OpticalSystemSolver.muellerMatrixR()` / `muellerMatrixT()` (`Solvers.fs:315,316`); this part MUST NOT add a second system-level Mueller routine. The Stokes vector per field is read from `EmField.stokesVector` (`FieldFunctions.fs:44`); the per-`Solution` incident/reflected/transmitted Stokes vectors are read from `Solution.stokesI`/`stokesR`/`stokesT` (`FieldFunctions.fs:222,227,238`). A new pure function `stokesSystem (s : Solution) : StokesSystem` in `Analytics/AnalysisFunctions.fs` MUST assemble the existing-but-unconstructed `StokesSystem` record (`Fields.fs:590`) from those three accessors. The Jones matrices MUST be read from `JonesMatrix.fromEmFields` (`Fields.fs:679`); no Jones algebra is re-implemented.

### R-4. §F.4 [Standard] Degree of polarization MUST be derived from the existing Stokes vector

The degree of polarization MUST be a new pure function `degreeOfPolarization (StokesVector v) : float` in `Analytics/AnalysisFunctions.fs`, computed as `sqrt(s1² + s2² + s3²) / s0` from the four components of the `StokesVector` (`Fields.fs:580`), reusing `Solution.stokesR`/`stokesT` (`FieldFunctions.fs:227,238`) as its inputs. Ellipticity and azimuth are NOT re-derived here — they are already exposed as `EmFieldSystem.ellipticityR`/`ellipticityT`/`azimuthR`/`azimuthT` (`FieldFunctions.fs:157,161,165,169`) and as the `EllipticityR`/`EllipticityT`/`AzimuthR`/`AzimuthT` `OpticalFunction` cases (`FieldFunctions.fs:119-122,184-187`); this part MUST surface those existing functions, not new ones.

### R-5. §F.5 [Standard] Ellipsometric Ψ, Δ and (N, C, S) MUST be derived from the reflected s/p amplitudes

A new module-level set of pure functions `psiDelta (s : Solution) : float * float` and `ncs (s : Solution) : float * float * float` MUST be added to `Analytics/AnalysisFunctions.fs`. They MUST form the complex ellipsometric ratio ρ = r_pp / r_ss from the reflected field's s- and p-resolved amplitudes `EmField.amplitudeS` / `EmField.amplitudeP` (`Fields.fs:520,530`) taken from the reflected solutions of `OpticalSystemSolver.solutionS()` / `solutionP()` (`Solvers.fs:313,314`) — reusing the exact s/p decomposition that `getMuellerMatrix` already relies on (`Solvers.fs:286`). Ψ and Δ MUST be `tan Ψ = |ρ|`, `Δ = arg ρ`; the (N, C, S) triple MUST be `N = cos 2Ψ`, `C = sin 2Ψ cos Δ`, `S = sin 2Ψ sin Δ`. These functions MUST NOT call into the optimizer and MUST NOT introduce a new field-amplitude extraction path; `amplitudeS`/`amplitudeP` are the single source. Part G §G.6 reuses this same s/p ellipsometric derivation for fit residuals and MUST NOT fork it. Ψ/Δ-vs-λ and Ψ/Δ-vs-angle plots reuse `calculate`/`plot` by mapping these functions over the per-point `Solution`, mirroring how `Charting.plot` maps `Solution.func` (`Charting.fs:26-31`).

### R-6. §F.6 [Standard] In-layer field / EFI depth profile MUST be sampled via the existing `EmField.propagate` seam

The |E|²/Poynting-vs-depth profile MUST be produced by a new pure function `fieldDepthProfile (system : OpticalSystem) (info : IncidentLightInfo) (samplesPerLayer : int) : (double<meter> * float) list` in a new file `Analytics/FieldProfile.fs`. It MUST walk the transmitted `EmField` of the base solution into each `Layer` (`Media.fs:24`) by repeatedly applying the inter-element propagation seam `EmField.propagate (s : Layer)` (`BerremanMatrix.fs:224`) at sub-layer thickness steps cut from the layer's `Thickness` (`Media.fs:12`), and at each depth read `EmField.e` for |E|² and `EmField.s` (the Poynting vector, `Fields.fs:434`) for power flow. It MUST reuse `BaseOpticalSystemSolver` (`Solvers.fs:115`) to obtain the entry field and MUST NOT re-solve the 4×4 system per depth sample. The known limitation noted in the engine (`BerremanMatrix.fs:221`, "Does not work properly yet") is carried forward as-is — this part wires the profile through that seam and MUST NOT attempt to rewrite `propagate`. The depth axis is stored in meters; nm/µm display is the UI boundary's concern (Part A §A.10).

### R-7. §F.7 [Standard] Per-layer absorptance and total absorbed power MUST be derived from the Poynting flux at layer boundaries

A new pure function `layerAbsorptance (system : OpticalSystem) (info : IncidentLightInfo) : (Layer * float) list` and a `totalAbsorbedPower` aggregate MUST be added to `Analytics/FieldProfile.fs`. Each layer's absorptance MUST be the drop in normal Poynting flux across that layer, computed from `EmField.s` (`Fields.fs:434`) of the propagated field at the layer's upper and lower boundaries using the same `EmField.propagate (Layer)` walk as F.6 (`BerremanMatrix.fs:224`); the per-field intensity normalisation MUST reuse `EmField.intensity` (`FieldFunctions.fs:69`) against the incident field. The total absorbed power MUST equal the system-level A from F.1 within solver tolerance, and the function MUST NOT introduce a second absorption definition divergent from `absorptance` (F.1). No new energy-balance constant is introduced.

### R-8. §F.8 [Standard] Color (CIE XYZ / Lab / sRGB) MUST convert an R or T spectrum sampled over the `WaveLengthRange`

A new file `Analytics/Colorimetry.fs` MUST provide pure functions `spectrumToXyz`, `xyzToLab`, and `xyzToSrgb`. `spectrumToXyz` MUST take the `(float * Solution) array` produced by `Variables.calculate` over a `WaveLengthRange` (`Variables.fs:46,237`) plus a chosen channel (`R` or `T` via the `OpticalFunction` cases, `FieldFunctions.fs:130,133`), integrate the channel against the CIE 1931 2° colour-matching functions and a chosen illuminant, and return CIE XYZ; `xyzToLab` and `xyzToSrgb` MUST apply the standard CIE Lab and sRGB transforms. The CIE colour-matching tables and the D65/A illuminant tables are embedded constants in this file (the only net-new numeric data this part introduces, traced to 010 §4 "Color calculation"). These functions MUST consume the sweep output of F.1 and MUST NOT re-run the solver. No alternate colour space beyond XYZ/Lab/sRGB is added.

### R-9. §F.9 [Standard] Convergence control MUST expose ONLY the existing `SolverParameters.numberOfReflections`

The convergence control surfaced to analysis MUST be the existing field `SolverParameters.numberOfReflections` (`Solvers.fs:15`), threaded into `OpticalSystemSolver(info, system, parameters)` (`Solvers.fs:199`) at the point where this part constructs a solution for a thick `Plate`/`Wedge` substrate (`Media.fs:40`). This part MUST NOT invent new numerical thresholds, MUST NOT re-tune `almostZero` or `almostZeroDet` (`Constants.fs:41,45`), and MUST NOT add a convergence-iteration cache. The default MUST remain `SolverParameters.defaultValue` (`Solvers.fs:21`, `numberOfReflections = 3`) when the caller supplies none, matching what `calculate` already passes (`Variables.fs:266`).

### R-10. §F.10 All new analysis functions MUST live in the Analytics project and be reachable from the orchestration layer

The new files `Analytics/AnalysisFunctions.fs` (F.1, F.3, F.4, F.5), `Analytics/FieldProfile.fs` (F.6, F.7), and `Analytics/Colorimetry.fs` (F.8) MUST be added to `Analytics/Analytics.fsproj` (`C:/GitHub/Berreman/Berreman/Analytics/Analytics.fsproj:39` shows the `<Compile Include="...">` ordering convention) in dependency order after `FieldFunctions`/`Variables`. They MUST be plain F# modules of pure functions over `Solution`/`EmField`/`OpticalSystem` with no UI, no FuncUI reference (the clone audit gate of Part A §A.9 is unaffected and remains undecided), and no hidden global state. The `OpticalConstructor.Ui` project (Part A assembly layout) consumes them by import; this part MUST NOT add a UI page itself. The completion of `em.muellerMatrix` (F.3) is an edit to the existing `FieldFunctions.fs:93`, not a new file.

## Non-requirements

- Alternate optimization-driven analyses are OUT OF SCOPE — owned by Part G (slices 009-011).
- Chart rendering / a UI page is OUT OF SCOPE — owned by Part H (and the Ui charts files); this part adds no UI page itself (§F.10).
- Caching of sweep results beyond the §A.7 `.binz` sidecar, retry/resume of long sweeps, and any incremental-cache layer are OUT OF SCOPE (§F.0 scope boundary, §F.2, constraint 6).
- Schema-versioning of the new result records is OUT OF SCOPE (§F.0 scope boundary).
- A new math-seam backend is OUT OF SCOPE; no `almostZero`/`almostZeroDet` re-tuning, no new numerical threshold (§F.9, §F.0).
- No new C# project; no UI; no FuncUI reference — the clone audit gate is unaffected per §F.10 (constraints 1 / 5).

